ue:** This is in a shared file (not new to this PR) but worth noting since it is exercised by the new Copilot CLI E2E agent.\\n\\n```go\\nsetCmd := exec.Command(\\\"tmux\\\", \\\"set-option\\\", \\\"-t\\\", name, \\\"remain-on-exit\\\", \\\"on\\\")\\n_ = setCmd.Run()\\n```\\n\\nIf this fails, when the copilot process exits unexpectedly, the tmux pane will be destroyed before the E2E harness can capture the error output. This makes debugging impossible.\\n\\n**Severity:** MEDIUM -- Pre-existing pattern but impacts Copilot E2E test debuggability.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## FINDING 11 -- MEDIUM: `Capture()` in tmux.go silently discards errors\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/e2e/agents/tmux.go`, line 164\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *TmuxSession) Capture() string {\\n    cmd := exec.Command(\\\"tmux\\\", \\\"capture-pane\\\", \\\"-t\\\", s.name, \\\"-p\\\")\\n    out, _ := cmd.Output()\\n    return strings.TrimRight(string(out), \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n}\\n```\\n\\nIf `tmux capture-pane` fails (e.g., session was killed), the function returns an empty string. Callers in `WaitFor` and `Send` compare this empty string against patterns and previous snapshots, leading to confusing behavior.\\n\\n**Severity:** MEDIUM -- Pre-existing pattern but impacts Copilot E2E test reliability.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## POSITIVE OBSERVATIONS\\n\\nThe following areas demonstrate good error handling practices:\\n\\n1. **`ReadAndParseHookInput`** (`event.go`) -- Properly checks for empty input, wraps read errors, and wraps parse errors with context. This is the gold standard for the codebase.\\n\\n2. **`InstallHooks` file write path** (`hooks.go`, lines 138-149) -- Properly checks `MkdirAll`, `json.Marshal`, and `os.WriteFile` with wrapped errors. Each failure point has a descriptive message.\\n\\n3. **`WriteSession` validation** (`copilotcli.go`, lines 106-128) -- Validates nil session, wrong agent, empty session ref, and empty native data before attempting the write. Each returns a distinct error