ostic output.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## FINDING 7 -- MEDIUM: Transcript extraction functions silently skip malformed data payloads\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/transcript.go`, lines 100-131 (`extractModifiedFilesFromEvents`), lines 134-153 (`extractPromptsFromEvents`), lines 156-173 (`extractSummaryFromEvents`)\\n\\n**Issue:** All three functions use `json.Unmarshal(events[i].Data, &data)` with `continue` on error. This means if the Copilot CLI transcript format changes (e.g., the `data` field structure changes for `tool.execution_complete`), the code silently produces empty results instead of surfacing that the expected data could not be parsed.\\n\\n```go\\nvar data toolExecCompleteData\\nif err := json.Unmarshal(events[i].Data, &data); err != nil {\\n    continue\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Hidden Errors:** Schema changes in the Copilot CLI transcript format, corrupted data fields, unexpected null values -- all silently skipped.\\n\\n**User Impact:** If Copilot CLI changes its event schema, users will suddenly have empty file change lists, empty prompts, and empty summaries in their checkpoints. There will be no error message explaining why.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** This is a reasonable tradeoff for JSONL parsing where some events may have different shapes, but there should be at least a counter or debug log. Consider logging when 100% of events of an expected type fail to parse (that indicates a schema change, not a single corrupt event).\\n\\n**Severity:** MEDIUM -- Acceptable for individual malformed events, but could mask a systematic format change.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## FINDING 8 -- MEDIUM: `resolveTranscriptRef` falls back to empty string on error\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/lifecycle.go`, lines 134-141\\n\\n**Issue:** When `GetSessionDir` fails, the function logs a warning and returns an empty string. This empty string then becomes `event.SessionRef`, which 