\\n**User Impact:** In E2E tests, if `SendKeys` fails silently, the test continues waiting for a prompt that will never appear, eventually timing out with a misleading \\\"timed out waiting for prompt\\\" error instead of \\\"tmux send-keys failed.\\\"\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Check the `SendKeys` error and return it. The `Close()` errors are less critical (cleanup), but at minimum log them.\\n\\n```go\\nif err := s.SendKeys(\\\"Enter\\\"); err != nil {\\n    _ = s.Close()\\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"dismissing startup dialog: %w\\\", err)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Severity:** MEDIUM -- Only affects E2E tests, but makes test failures harder to diagnose.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## FINDING 10 -- MEDIUM: `tmux set-option` error silently discarded\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/e2e/agents/tmux.go`, lines 54-55\\n\\n**Issue:** This is in a shared file (not new to this PR) but worth noting since it is exercised by the new Copilot CLI E2E agent.\\n\\n```go\\nsetCmd := exec.Command(\\\"tmux\\\", \\\"set-option\\\", \\\"-t\\\", name, \\\"remain-on-exit\\\", \\\"on\\\")\\n_ = setCmd.Run()\\n```\\n\\nIf this fails, when the copilot process exits unexpectedly, the tmux pane will be destroyed before the E2E harness can capture the error output. This makes debugging impossible.\\n\\n**Severity:** MEDIUM -- Pre-existing pattern but impacts Copilot E2E test debuggability.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## FINDING 11 -- MEDIUM: `Capture()` in tmux.go silently discards errors\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/e2e/agents/tmux.go`, line 164\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *TmuxSession) Capture() string {\\n    cmd := exec.Command(\\\"tmux\\\", \\\"capture-pane\\\", \\\"-t\\\", s.name, \\\"-p\\\")\\n    out, _ := cmd.Output()\\n    return strings.TrimRight(string(out), \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n}\\n```\\n\\nIf `tmux capture-pane` fails (e.g., session was killed), the function returns an empty string. Callers in `WaitFor` and `Send` compare this empty string against patterns and previo