sive review.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Code Review Report: `alex/add-copilot-agent` PR\\n\\n### Files Reviewed\\n\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/copilotcli.go` (agent interface impl)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/hooks.go` (hook install/uninstall)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/lifecycle.go` (hook event parsing)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/transcript.go` (transcript analysis)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/types.go` (type definitions)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` (agent registration)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` (hook command import)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` (shared lifecycle changes)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle_test.go` (lifecycle tests)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/e2e/agents/copilot-cli.go` (E2E test agent)\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/e2e/agents/tmux.go` (tmux session changes)\\n- All `*_test.go` files in the `copilotcli` package\\n- `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/scripts/test-copilot-cli-agent-integration.sh` (probe script)\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThis is a well-structured agent integration that closely follows the patterns established by the existing agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Gemini, OpenCode, Factory AI Droid). The code demonstrates strong adherence to project conventions: proper error handling, logging patterns, interface compliance, and comprehensive test coverage. The `resolveTaskPreUntrackedFiles` fallback in the shared lifecycle is a thoughtful design for agents lacking a `SubagentStart` hook.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Critical (90-100): No Issues Found\\n\\nNo critical bugs or security vulnerabilities were identified.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Important (80-89)\\n\\n**Issue 1: E2E `RunPrompt` does not apply `TimeoutMultiplier` (Confidence: 85)**\\n\\nFile: `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/e2e/agents/copilot-cli.go`, lines 62-65\\n\\nThe `TimeoutMultiplier()` method returns `1.5`, but `RunPrompt` uses the raw `cfg.PromptTimeout` or a 60-second default without applying the multiplier. Other agents that define `TimeoutMultiplier` rely on the E2E framework to apply it externally, but you should verify the framework actually calls `TimeoutMultiplier()` and multiplies it into `cfg.PromptTimeout` before it reaches `RunPrompt`. If the framework does NOT apply it, then this method returns 1.5 but has no effect on `RunPrompt`.\\n\\n```go\\ntimeout := 60 * time.Second\\nif cfg.PromptTimeout > 0 {\\n    timeout = cfg.PromptTimeout\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSuggestion: Verify the E2E framework multiplies timeouts before calling `RunPrompt`. If not, apply `c.TimeoutMultiplier()` to the timeout here.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Issue 2: `resolveTranscriptRef` silently returns empty string on error (Confidence: 82)**\\n\\nFile: `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/cmd/entire/cli/agent/copilotcli/lifecycle.go`, lines 121-128\\n\\nWhen `GetSessionDir` fails, `resolveTranscriptRef` returns an empty string for `SessionRef`. The downstream `TurnStart` event will have `SessionRef: \\\"\\\"`, which means the framework's `handleLifecycleTurnStart` will need to handle this gracefully. This is correctly documented as a limitation (transcriptPath is only in `agentStop`), and the `TurnEnd` handler will get the actual path from the `agentStop` payload. However, any code that assumes `SessionRef` is non-empty on `TurnStart` events could fail silently.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (c *CopilotCLIAgent) resolveTranscriptRef(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) string {\\n    sessionDir, err := c.GetSessionDir(sessionID)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        logging.Warn(ctx, \\\"copilot-cli: failed to resolve transcript path\\\", \\\"err\\\", err)\\n      