12→| Help available | PASS | Full `--help` with subcommands |\\n    13→| Version info | PASS | `0.0.420` |\\n    14→| Hook keywords | PASS | 8 hook types in `.github/hooks/*.json` |\\n    15→| Session keywords | PASS | `--resume`, `--continue`, `--share` |\\n    16→| Config directory | PASS | `~/.copilot/` (user-level), `.github/hooks/` (repo-level) |\\n    17→| Documentation | PASS | docs.github.com/en/copilot/reference/hooks-configuration |\\n    18→\\n    19→## Binary\\n    20→\\n    21→- Name: `copilot`\\n    22→- Version: `0.0.420` (GA as of 2026-02-25)\\n    23→- Install: `brew install copilot-cli` or `npm install -g @github/copilot`\\n    24→\\n    25→## Hook Mechanism\\n    26→\\n    27→- Config file: `.github/hooks/*.json` (all JSON files in directory are auto-discovered)\\n    28→- Our file: `.github/hooks/entire.json` (dedicated file, avoids conflicts)\\n    29→- Config format: JSON\\n    30→- Hook registration: Array of hook entries per event name, each with `type: \\\"command\\\"` and `bash` field\\n    31→\\n    32→### Hook Config Format\\n    33→\\n    34→```json\\n    35→{\\n    36→  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n    37→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    38→    \\\"hookName\\\": [\\n    39→      {\\n    40→        \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n    41→        \\\"bash\\\": \\\"entire hooks copilot-cli hook-name\\\"\\n    42→      }\\n    43→    ]\\n    44→  }\\n    45→}\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→Note: Uses `bash` key (not `command` like Claude Code/Gemini). Also supports `powershell` for Windows. Each entry can have optional `cwd`, `timeoutSec` (default 30), `env`, and `comment` fields.\\n    49→\\n    50→### Hook Names and Event Mapping\\n    51→\\n    52→| Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Stdin Payload Fields | Entire EventType |\\n    53→|-----------------|---------------|---------------------|-----------------|\\n    54→| `userPromptSubmitted` | User submits a prompt | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `prompt` | `TurnStart` |\\n    55→| `sessionStart` | Agent session begins/resumes | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `source`, `initialPrompt` | `SessionStart` |\\n    56→| `agentStop` | Agent finishes a turn | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `transcriptPath`, `stopReason` | `TurnEnd` |\\n    57→| `sessionEnd` | Session completed/terminated | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `reason` | `SessionEnd` |\\n    58→| `subagentStop` | Subagent finishes | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, *(TBD — needs capture)* | `SubagentEnd` |\\n    59→| `preToolUse` | Before tool execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    60→| `postToolUse` | After tool execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    61→| `errorOccurred` | Error during execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    62→\\n    63→**Event ordering quirk:** `userPromptSubmitted` fires BEFORE `sessionStart` on the first prompt. This matches Claude Code's behavior and the framework's session phase state machine handles it correctly (TurnStart can arrive before SessionStart).\\n    64→\\n    65→**Valid Entire EventTypes:** `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n    66→\\n    67→### Hook Input Payloads (Captured)\\n    68→\\n    69→**userPromptSubmitted:**\\n    70→```json\\n    71→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480081360,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"prompt\\\":\\\"hi\\\"}\\n    72→```\\n    73→\\n    74→**sessionStart:**\\n    75→```json\\n    76→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480081383,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"initialPrompt\\\":\\\"hi\\\"}\\n    77→```\\n    78→\\n    79→**agentStop:**\\n    80→```json\\n    81→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480085412,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"transcriptPath\\\":\\\"/home/user/.copilot/session-state/b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b/events.jsonl\\\",\\\"stopReason\\\":\\\"end_turn\\\"}\\n    82→```\\n    83→\\n    84→**sessionEnd:**\\n    85→```json\\n    86→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480085425,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"complete\\\"}\\n    87→```\\n    88→\\n    89→## Transcript\\n    90→\\n    91→- Location: `~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/events.jsonl`\\n    92→- Format: JSONL (one JSON object per line)\\n    93→- Session ID extraction: `sessionId` field in hook payloads (UUID format)\\n    94→- Session ID format: UUID (`b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b`)\\n    95→\\n    96→### Transcript Entry Schema\\n    97→\\n    98→Each line has: `type`, `data`, `id` (UUID), `timestamp` (ISO 8601), `parentId`\\n    99→\\n   100→**Event types observed:**\\n   101→- `session.start` — Session metadata (sessionId, version, producer, copilotVersion, context)\\n   102→- `user.message` — User messages (`content`, `transformedContent`, `attachments`, `interactionId`)\\n   103→- `assistant.turn_start` — Start of assistant turn (`turnId`, `interactionId`)\\n   104→- `assistant.message` — Assistant response (`content`, `toolRequests[]`, `reasoningText`)\\n   105→- `tool.execution_complete` — Tool result (`toolCallId`, `toolTelemetry.properties.filePaths` (JSON-encoded string array), `linesAdded`, `linesRemoved`)\\n   106→- `assistant.turn_end` — End of assistant turn (`turnId`)\\n   107→\\n   108→**Example entries:**\\n   109→```jsonl\\n   110→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"session.start\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"4de47255-...\\\",\\\"version\\\":1,\\\"producer\\\":\\\"copilot-agent\\\",\\\"copilotVersion\\\":\\\"0.0.420\\\",\\\"startTime\\\":\\\"2026-03-02T01:11:45.379Z\\\",\\\"context\\\":{\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"gitRoot\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"branch\\\":\\\"main\\\",\\\"repository\\\":\\\"org/repo\\\"}},\\\"id\\\":\\\"c1c1...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-03-02T01:11:45.421Z\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":null}\\n   111→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user.message\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"content\\\":\\\"exit\\\",\\\"transformedContent\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"attachments\\\":[],\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"20fa...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"00ac...\\\"}\\n   112→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.turn_start\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"turnId\\\":\\\"0\\\",\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"3b61...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"20fa...\\\"}\\n   113→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.message\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"messageId\\\":\\\"a078...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"To exit...\\\",\\\"toolRequests\\\":[],\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\",\\\"reasoningText\\\":\\\"...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"c892...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"aaeb...\\\"}\\n   114→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.turn_end\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"turnId\\\":\\\"0\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"0ae4...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"4989...\\\"}\\n   115→```\\n   116→\\n   117→### Tool Usage in Transcripts\\n   118→\\n   119→The `assistant.message` entries have a `toolRequests` array with tool call IDs. After each tool executes, a `tool.execution_complete` event is emitted with `toolTelemetry.properties.filePaths`, where `filePaths` is a string containing a JSON array of file paths modified by that tool call. The `TranscriptAnalyzer` implementation parses this `filePaths` property to extract modified files for checkpoint metadata.\\n   120→\\n   121→**Note:** Token usage is NOT available in the Copilot CLI JSONL format. The transcript events do not include input/output token counts or cost information, so `TokenCalculator` is not implemented.\\n   122→\\n   123→### Transcript Position\\n   124→\\n   125→Position = line count (JSONL format). Use `agent.ChunkJSONL()` / `agent.ReassembleJSONL()` for chunking.\\n   126→\\n   127→### TranscriptAnalyzer\\n   128→\\n   129→The `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface is implemented for Copilot CLI, providing:\\n   130→- `GetTranscriptPosition` — counts JSONL lines (lightweight, no JSON parsing)\\n   131→- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — collects `filePaths` from `tool.execution_complete` events after a given line offset\\n   132→- `ExtractPrompts` — collects `content` from `user.message` events\\n   133→- `ExtractSummary` — returns the `content` of the last `assistant.message` event\\n   134→\\n   135→## Session State Directory\\n   136→\\n   137→```\\n   138→~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/\\n   139→├── events.jsonl          # Transcript (JSONL)\\n   140→├── workspace.yaml        # Workspace metadata (cwd, git info, summary)\\n   141→├── checkpoints/          # Agent's own checkpoints\\n   142→├── files/                # File snapshots\\n   143→├── research/             # Research data\\n   144→└── rewind-snapshots/     # Agent's rewind snapshots\\n   145→```\\n   146→\\n   147→## Config Preservation\\n   148→\\n   149→- Hook config is in `.github/hooks/*.json` — each file is auto-discovered\\n   150→- We create a **dedicated** `.github/hooks/entire.json` file, leaving other hook files untouched\\n   151→- No need for read-modify-write of existing files\\n   152→- If `entire.json` already exists, read-modify-write to preserve any user additions\\n   153→\\n   154→## CLI Flags\\n   155→\\n   156→- Non-interactive prompt: `copilot -p \\\"prompt\\\" --allow-all-tools`\\n   157→- Interactive with initial prompt: `copilot -i \\\"prompt\\\"`\\n   158→- Interactive mode: `copilot`\\n   159→- Resume most recent: `copilot --continue`\\n   160→- Resume specific: `copilot --resume <sessionId>`\\n   161→- Autopilot (no confirmations): `copilot --autopilot`\\n   162→- Config directory: `--config-dir <dir>` (default: `~/.copilot`)\\n   163→- Relevant env vars: `COPILOT_ALLOW_ALL` (equivalent to `--allow-all-tools`)\\n   164→\\n   165→## Presence Detection\\n   166→\\n   167→- No repo-level `.copilot/` directory (unlike other agents)\\n   168→- `DetectPresence` delegates to `AreHooksInstalled`, which reads `.github/hooks/entire.json` and checks if any hook entry has an Entire command prefix (`entire ` or `go run ${COPILOT_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go `)\\n   169→- Simply having a `.github/hooks/` directory is NOT sufficient -- the directory must contain `entire.json` with Entire hook entries\\n   170→- Alternative: check for `copilot` binary in PATH\\n   171→\\n   172→## Protected Directories\\n   173→\\n   174→- `.github` — contains hook configs (committed to repo, unlikely to be affected by rewind)\\n   175→- No agent-specific repo directory to protect\\n   176→\\n   177→## Subagent Lifecycle\\n   178→\\n   179→Copilot CLI has **one-sided** subagent hooks: `subagentStop` fires but `subagentStart` does NOT\\n   180→(tested by registering the hook — Copilot CLI ignores it). The transcript does contain\\n   181→`subagent.started` / `subagent.completed` events with `toolCallId`, but these are not\\n   182→surfaced as hooks.\\n   183→\\n   184→The `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` hooks fire with `toolName: \\\"task\\\"` for subagent lifecycle,\\n   185→which could be used as an alternative mechanism for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd` in the future.\\n   186→\\n   187→Because there is no `SubagentStart` hook, the framework cannot capture pre-task state (untracked\\n   188→files snapshot). The `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd` dispatcher falls back to the session's\\n   189→pre-prompt state to avoid spurious task checkpoints from pre-existing untracked files\\n   190→(e.g., `.github/hooks/entire.json`).\\n   191→\\n   192→## Gaps & Limitations\\n   193→\\n   194→- No `Compaction` event — Copilot CLI doesn't appear to have a context compaction hook\\n   195→- No `SubagentStart` hook — only `subagentStop` fires; framework falls back to pre-prompt state\\n   196→- `subagentStop` payload fields beyond `timestamp`/`cwd`/`sessionId` not yet fully captured\\n   197→- `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` payloads not yet leveraged (could provide SubagentStart equivalent)\\n   198→- Tool request schema in transcripts needs verification with a real tool-using session\\n   199→- `transcriptPath` only available in `agentStop` hook — `userPromptSubmitted` and `sessionStart` don't include it, so we compute it from `~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/events.jsonl`\\n   200→\\n   201→## Captured Payloads\\n   202→\\n   203→- Hook capture logs: `tmp/test-copilot/logs/copilot-hooks.jsonl`\\n   204→- Local transcript: `~/.copilot/session-state/4de47255-3d43-4938-b8fa-b6e49f1d0aca/events.jsonl`\\n   205→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"853709ac-7a98-4433-9411-0b40e2ff43fe\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T06:31:55.949Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a01552b27c09aea9a\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_012D2rSW6wxQ8Ps1Gf8waiqf\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01HnP3u7kPoX71YSh5ibbFdP\",\"uuid\":\"dfadd589-1edc-4a8a-b921-0d8f7150bfa7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T06:31:56.009Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"dfadd589-1edc-4a8a-b921-0d8f7150bfa7\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5\",\"sessionId\":\"e73fdc2e-be24-417b-a111-12fff5857e65\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"shiny-herding-gosling\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T06:31:56.036Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_0158qDwhLtcH62e69HHo4ogp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01LX5foEaeGf95MAtYUFFHcC\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5/.github/copilot-instructions.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":6,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":671,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":95867,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":671},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYha6G9YGQCMZFaGLTrUi\",\"uuid\":\"720f80b2-6d56-4f85-b832-94b69f004ff0\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a01552b27c09aea9a\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_012D2rSW6wxQ8Ps1Gf8waiqf\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01HnP3u7kPoX71YSh5ibbFdP\",\"uuid\":\"c0cce51c-02ce-4746-8c9b-9b96a341d127\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T06:31:56.036Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c0cce51c-02ce-4746-8c9b-9b96a341d127\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/5\",\"sessionId\":\"e73fdc2e-be24-417b-a111-12fff5857e65\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"shiny-herding-gosling\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01LX5foEaeGf95MAtYUFFHcC\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Copilot Instructions for Entire CLI\\n     2→\\n     3→## Repository Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→Entire CLI is a Go CLI tool that captures AI coding agent sessions (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.) as searchable metadata stored separately from code commits. It uses a strategy pattern for session/checkpoint management with minimal impact on commit history.\\n     6→\\n     7→**Tech Stack**: Go (version in `mise.toml`), Cobra (CLI), charmbracelet/huh (interactive prompts), go-git/v5 (with caveats)\\n     8→\\n     9→## Build & Validation Commands\\n    10→\\n    11→All commands use `mise` as the task runner. Always run these in order before committing:\\n    12→\\n    13→```bash\\n    14→mise run fmt           # Format with gofmt (required - CI will fail otherwise)\\n    15→mise run lint          # Lint with golangci-lint (only new issues)\\n    16→mise run test          # Unit tests\\n    17→mise run test:ci       # Full tests with race detection (same as CI)\\n    18→```\\n    19→\\n    20→**CI runs these checks on every PR** (see `.github/workflows/`):\\n    21→1. gofmt formatting check (must pass - no unformatted files)\\n    22→2. golangci-lint\\n    23→3. go.mod tidy check\\n    24→4. All tests with race detection (`mise run test:ci`)\\n    25→\\n    26→## Critical Code Patterns\\n    27→\\n    28→### Error Handling\\n    29→\\n    30→The CLI uses `SilentError` to avoid duplicate error output (see `errors.go`):\\n    31→\\n    32→```go\\n    33→// When you print a custom error message, return SilentError\\n    34→fmt.Fprintln(cmd.ErrOrStderr(), \\\"User-friendly error message\\\")\\n    35→return NewSilentError(errors.New(\\\"internal error\\\"))\\n    36→\\n    37→// For normal errors, just return them - main.go will print\\n    38→return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to do X: %w\\\", err)\\n    39→```\\n    40→\\n    41→### Forbidden go-git Operations\\n    42→\\n    43→**NEVER use go-git v5's Reset or Checkout directly** - they delete `.gitignore`d directories.\\n    44→\\n    45→```go\\n    46→// WRONG - deletes .entire/ and .worktrees/\\n    47→worktree.Reset(&git.ResetOptions{Mode: git.HardReset, Commit: hash})\\n    48→worktree.Checkout(&git.CheckoutOptions{Branch: ref})\\n    49→\\n    50→// CORRECT - use CLI wrappers from strategy/common.go and git_operations.go\\n    51→HardResetWithProtection(hash)\\n    52→CheckoutBranch(branch)\\n    53→```\\n    54→\\n    55→### Path Handling\\n    56→\\n    57→**NEVER use `os.Getwd()` for git-relative paths** - breaks when running from subdirectories.\\n    58→\\n    59→```go\\n    60→// WRONG - breaks in subdirectories\\n    61→cwd, _ := os.Getwd()\\n    62→absPath := filepath.Join(cwd, gitRelativePath)\\n    63→\\n    64→// CORRECT - always use repo root\\n    65→repoRoot, _ := paths.RepoRoot()\\n    66→absPath := filepath.Join(repoRoot, gitRelativePath)\\n    67→```\\n    68→\\n    69→The linter enforces these patterns via `forbidigo` rules in `.golangci.yaml`.\\n    70→\\n    71→### Accessibility\\n    72→\\n    73→Interactive prompts must support screen readers:\\n    74→\\n    75→```go\\n    76→// In cli package - use NewAccessibleForm()\\n    77→form := NewAccessibleForm(huh.NewGroup(...))\\n    78→\\n    79→// In strategy package - check isAccessibleMode()\\n    80→form := huh.NewForm(huh.NewGroup(...))\\n    81→if isAccessibleMode() {\\n    82→    form = form.WithAccessible(true)\\n    83→}\\n    84→```\\n    85→\\n    86→### Logging vs User Output\\n    87→\\n    88→- **Internal/debug logging**: Use `logging.Debug/Info/Warn/Error(ctx, msg, attrs...)` from `cli/logging/`. Writes to `.entire/logs/`.\\n    89→- **User-facing output**: Use `fmt.Fprint*(cmd.OutOrStdout(), ...)` or `cmd.ErrOrStderr()`.\\n    90→\\n    91→Don't use `fmt.Print*` for operational messages (checkpoint saves, hook invocations) - use the `logging` package.\\n    92→\\n    93→**Privacy**: Don't log user content (prompts, file contents, commit messages). Log only operational metadata (IDs, counts, paths, durations).\\n    94→\\n    95→## Project Structure\\n    96→\\n    97→```\\n    98→cmd/entire/\\n    99→├── main.go           # Entry point\\n   100→└── cli/              # Main CLI package\\n   101→    ├── strategy/     # Session checkpoint strategies (strategy pattern)\\n   102→    ├── checkpoint/   # Low-level storage operations\\n   103→    ├── session/      # Session state management (.git/entire-sessions/)\\n   104→    ├── agent/        # AI agent abstraction layer\\n   105→    ├── paths/        # Path utilities (RepoRoot)\\n   106→    └── integration_test/  # Integration tests (//go:build integration)\\n   107→```\\n   108→\\n   109→**Key configuration files**:\\n   110→- `mise.toml` - Task definitions and Go version\\n   111→- `.golangci.yaml` - Linting rules (forbidigo patterns for unsafe operations)\\n   112→- `go.mod` - Module dependencies\\n   113→\\n   114→For detailed architecture documentation, see `CLAUDE.md`.\\n   115→\\n   116→## T